The paper deals with adaptive video streaming over HTTP, which involves multimedia (MM) and network infrastructure (NI) aspects. The proposed algorithm is designed to optimize the play-out strategy, which is a key component of video streaming systems, and thus falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (DC). The evaluation of the algorithm involves measuring the performance of video streaming in terms of smoothness and bit-rate switches, which are related to the quality of service (QoS) and user experience (UX), and thus falls under the category of software engineering (SD) and information theory (IT).
